      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "Bke6usYzKr",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "Their main results can be summarized as follows.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "Bke6usYzKr",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "1. If only the second layer is optimized, they observe the double-descent phenomenon.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_fact",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "Bke6usYzKr",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "2. However, if only the first layer is optimized, the double-descent is not observed.",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "Bke6usYzKr",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "This shows that recent results for certain linear models (e.g. Song, Montanari 2019) do not directly transfer to neural networks.",
